The paper deals with image-based modeling of biomedical data, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a generative model and a latent variable model also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The application of the model to biomedical data further suggests that it could belong to the bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category. Finally, the use of the Hilbert-Schmitt Independence Criterion (HSIC) suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
